File: The lions are alleged to have been poisoned before their jaws and paws were removed. JOHANNESBURG - Police and wildlife officials are searching for those involved in the killing of four lions in Pretoria. Officials believe the lions were killed so their body parts could be used as muthi. READ: Two arrested as police raid Joburg's muthi market The animals are alleged to have been poisoned before their jaws and paws were removed. The big cats, from the Rietvlei nature reserve, were considered the pride of Tshwane.